editChangeNet(25.10)                                      editChangeNet(25.10)

Name
       editChangeNet - Changes the net associated with selected physical pins,
       wires, and vias

Syntax
       editChangeNet

       [-help]

       -to <netName>

       Changes  the  net  associated  with  selected physical pins, wires, and
       vias.

       You can also use editChangeNet to change the net name of the patch wire
       (pWire) generated by NanoRoute.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editChangeNet parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editChangeNet

       -to    Specifies the name of the net to which to  assign  the  selected
              physical pins, wires and vias.

Example
              * The  following  set  of  commands  selects  the physical pins,
                wires, and vias that belong to net VDD1 and reassigns them  to
                net VDD2:

                editSelect -net VDD1

                editChangeNet -to VDD2

